  "text": "Human HDL prepared by density gradient ultracentrifugation was provided by Drs J. Goldstein and M. Brown, University of Texas Southwestern. [CITATION_1] The HDL was isolated from healthy volunteers after a 12hour fast, and the HDL 3 subfraction (density range, 1.12-1.2181 g/mL) was obtained and used in all experiments. The HDL was stored at 4°C before use. The concentration used refers to the total protein concentration, with the majority of HDL protein being apoA-I.",
